· Orientation: Vertical fins (90° tilt). Reduces settling rate by ~80% compared to horizontal.
· Structure: Fixed aluminum truss towers (10m+ height). Exploits boundary layer physics where dust concentration drops sharply above 10m.
· Redundancy: Modular panels (10 kWₑ each). Loss of one panel does not compromise mission.

