4.5 Hybrid Cleaning Mechanism

Given the low-pressure EDS performance degradation observed experimentally (DRR < 20% at 700 Pa), SH-CORS adopts a multi-modal cleaning strategy:

1. EDS (Primary for loose dust, nominal pressure): Low-power traveling wave for loose dust. Effectiveness at Mars pressure requires TRL advancement.
2. Piezoelectric Vibration (Secondary): High-power bursts (50 W/m², 100 Hz) to break perchlorate cementation and agglomerated dust.
3. Thermal Shedding (Tertiary): Temperature cycling (ΔT ≈ 50 K) induces differential thermal expansion, shedding fused dust layers.
4. Mechanical Wiping (Emergency): Robotic arm with brush for EVA-assisted cleaning (redundancy).

Low-Pressure EDS Performance Improvement Strategies:

· Higher voltage operation (up to ±10 kV, validated for dielectric breakdown)
· Multi-frequency driving signals (not just two-phase)
· Pre-charging of dust particles via corona discharge
· Electrode geometry optimization (reduced spacing)

