5.3 Power Management Logic

During dust storms, solar power drops. The system prioritizes:

1. Life Support Power
2. Reactor Safety (Minimum Cooling)
3. EDS Cleaning (Reduced frequency)

Logic: Accept higher $T_s$ (up to 550 K) to reduce cleaning power demand during low-power events.

5.4 Emergency Heat Rejection Mode

If cleaning fails completely:

1. Passive Mode: Accept dust accumulation ($\epsilon \approx 0.5$)
2. Temperature Increase: Operate at 700 K maximum
3. Power Turndown: Reduce reactor output to 40%
4. Duration: Sustainable for 14 days
5. Recovery: EVA cleaning or panel replacement

